This article discusses the continuation of a national emergency declared in the United States in 1995 due to the actions of significant narcotics traffickers centered in Colombia. The national emergency was declared to address the threat posed to the national security, foreign policy, and economy of the United States, as well as the extreme levels of violence, corruption, and harm caused by these actions. The President has determined that the national emergency must continue beyond October 21, 2023, and has extended it for another year in accordance with the National Emergencies Act. This information has been published in the Federal Register and transmitted to Congress.